The 32-year-old pregnant woman and her four children killed last Sunday by gunmen in Anambra State have been buried in Onitsha, Their remains were interred at the Hausa Cementary in the state’s commercial hub amid tears. General Secretary, Arewa community in the state, Mahmud Imam, said in a  statement yesterday that the woman, Fatima Jibrin, and her children. were among  15 persons killed the same day in a series of attacks by “faceless and wicked people” in the state.   And God decided to show up, by Femi Adesina     Sen. Uba Sani wins Kaduna APC Gov ticket     Yilwada clinches Plateau APC Gov ticket   Imam said;  “What happened was on Sunday, May 22,  2022. We woke up peacefully but later in the day we started receiving calls from our members from various locations of the state that the so called unknown gunmen had launched a  series of attacks on them, which led to the deaths of about 15 persons. “That of Orumba local government was the most trending because involved a pregnant woman whose,  name is Fatima Jibrin and her four children. They were murdered in the middle of the road by these faceless and wicked people, called unknown gunmen.” The killings made Governor Charles Soludo to declare a dusk to dawn curfew in  Aguata, Ekwusigo, Ihiala, Nnewi North, Nnewi South, Orumba North, Orumba South and Ogbaru Local Government Areas. Soludo also banned Okada and shuttle bus operations on Mondays in the state till further notice.